The Davis Jaycees was the local branch of the  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Junior_Chamber United States Junior Chamber. The branch was shut down due to one of the most shocking incidents in Davis history. On November 19, 1983, police raided the Jaycees clubhouse, which was located between Davis and Woodland. Undercover officers discovered illegal sex acts, illegal gambling, illegal drug and alcohol sales, and the auctioning of a night with a prostitute. A total of 22 arrests were made.
